title: Grateful Dead Live at Fox Theater on 1980-04-29
lineage: FOB (Nakamichi 700)> Master Cassette(Sony TC-D5); A>D: Master Cassette (Tascam 112mkIII)>Sony R500 @44.1>; D>CD: DAT> MASTER CDR on HHB CDR 850> Duped to CD(1) on Tascam CD-D4000MKII; CD>SHN: EAC (see info)> Soundforge> CD WAV> SHNv3
description: Jack Straw, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Peggy-O, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, Far From Me, The Music Never Stopped Don't Ease Me In, Minglewood Blues, Ramble On Rose, Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> I Need A Miracle-> Bertha-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Good '80 show, stunning '80 aud If you like shows from 1980, especially the late spring/early summer period, this show will not disappoint.  I mainly wanted to comment on the quality of the aud itself, which is exceptional.  Truly.  Excellent work by Barry Glassberg.  I'd say 'once again' but this one stands out, in my opinion, as the best sounding aud he produced.  It's up there with the notable auds of 08-06-71 and 02-27-77.  The tunes?  All on the better side of competent, and a thoroughly enjoyable spring '80 show.  Five for the sound, four for the music.

Love the Fox!!! After Birmingham the night before we were all expecting something of a let down.  And while the song selection not as good this night, the boys were still on fire!!!! an over all danceable second set

Very solid AUD This recording is great.  I also really liked the show.  Favorites for me are Sailor > Saint.  The unusual jam after Terrapin is nice.  Good Lovin' closer is great material, as the crowd presence and enthusiasm within the tape is perfect.  The band has just enough pauses to let the audience participate there.  This is my first review.  If 3 means take it or leave it and 4 means take it, then 4-- take it.

Agree with those below - stunning sound+ For anyone that went to these shows they were great and in hindsight while the songs are short as Arista was trying to rebrand the Dead and make it more accessible they did not stop playing hard - First set is great  -Like Bob flubbing Minglewood with 'NY fillies' in Atlanta. Jerry fucks Terrapin up about the worst I have ever heard - not sure what was happening there at first ,mike problem or something.... They pull out of that and with jam 28+ mins (at first sounds like the Playin from 12/31/81).
Great Recording Very nice audience recording and fun show.  I will keep this review simple by saying you want this.  Seriously.
